name=Technology.NestedOptionsInSelect
rev=3
targets=Technology.NestedOptionsInSelect
text=[[#excerpt]]%0aFrom a recent php-general mailing list entry, someone was wondering how to set up a select block if you have nested items to select from. The way to do this is with the @@%3coptgroup>@@ tag, which, as the name suggests, groups sets of options:%0a[[#excerptend]]%0a%0a%0a(:source lang=html4strict linenum tabwidth=4:)%0a%3cp>A selection widget about cars. Notice groupings.%3c/p>%0a%3cselect>%0a	%3coptgroup label="Swedish Cars">%0a		%3coption value="volvo">Volvo%3c/option>%0a		%3coption value="saab">Saab%3c/option>%0a	%3c/optgroup>%0a	%3coptgroup label="German Cars">%0a		%3coption value="mercedes">Mercedes%3c/option>%0a		%3coption value="audi">Audi%3c/option>%0a	%3c/optgroup>%0a%3c/select>%0a(:sourceend:)%0a%0a:Unselected:Attach:ex1unselected.png%0a:Drop Down Enabled:Attach:ex1dropdown.png%0a%0a%0aAs you can see above, there are two groups, "Swedish Cars" and "German Cars" with different options inside of them.%0a%0aYou can put @@optgroup@@s inside of @@optgroup@@s for further nesting:%0a%0a(:source lang=html4strict linenum tabwidth=4:)%0a%3cp>Another selection widget about cars. Notice the nested groupings%3c/p>%0a%3cselect>%0a	%3coptgroup label="Swedish Cars">%0a		%3coptgroup label="&nbsp;Volvo">%0a			%3coption value="240s">240 Sedan%3c/option>%0a			%3coption value="240w">240 Wagon%3c/option>%0a			%3coption value="740s">740 Sedan%3c/option>%0a			%3coption value="740w">740 Wagon%3c/option>%0a		%3c/optgroup>%0a		%3coptgroup label="&nbsp;Saab">%0a			%3coption value="900s">900s%3c/option>%0a		%3c/optgroup>%0a	%3c/optgroup>%0a	%3coptgroup label="German Cars">%0a		%3coptgroup label="&nbsp;Mercedes">%0a			%3coption value="300SD">300SD%3c/option>%0a			%3coption value="S350">S350%3c/option>%0a			%3coption value="400SE">400SE%3c/option>%0a			%3coption value="500SEL">500SEL%3c/option>%0a			%3coption value="600SEL">600SEL%3c/option>%0a		%3c/optgroup>%0a		%3coptgroup label="&nbsp;Audi">%0a			%3coption value="2011TTSCoupe">2011 TTS Coupe%3c/option>%0a			%3coption value="2011TTSRoadster">2011 TTS Roadster%3c/option>%0a			%3coption value="S5Coupe">S5 Coupe%3c/option>%0a			%3coption value="S5Cabriolet">S5 Cabriolet%3c/option>%0a			%3coption value="S6Sedan">S6 Sedan%3c/option>%0a		%3c/optgroup>%0a	%3c/optgroup>%0a%3c/select>%0a(:sourceend:)%0a%0a%25note%25 Notice the use of the &amp;nbsp; in the example above to set off the supgroupings a little from the parent.%0a%0a:Unselected:Attach:ex2unselected.png%0a:Drop Down Enabled:Attach:ex2dropdown.png%0a%0a* [[http://portfolio.tamaratemple.com/htmlcssexamples/nestedoptions.shtml|Demo page]]%0a%0a!! Creating nested options via PHP%0a%0aThis should be drop dead easy, but I'll include an example anyway.%0a%0a(:source lang=php linenum tabwidth=4:)%0a%3c?php%0a$categories[] = array('id' => 1, 'name' => 'cars');%0a$categories[] = array('id' => 2, 'name' => 'trucks');%0a$categories[] = array('id' => 3, 'name' => 'motorcycles');%0a%0a$pages[] = array('id' => 1, 'name' => 'Neon', 'cat_id' => 1);%0a$pages[] = array('id' => 2, 'name' => 'Saturn', 'cat_id' => 1);%0a$pages[] = array('id' => 3, 'name' => 'F150', 'cat_id' => 2);%0a$pages[] = array('id' => 4, 'name' => 'Ram 2500', 'cat_id' => 2);%0a$pages[] = array('id' => 5, 'name' => 'Suzuki', 'cat_id' => 2);%0a$pages[] = array('id' => 6, 'name' => 'Honda', 'cat_id' => 3);%0a%0aecho "%3cselect id=\"page_id\">\n";%0a%0aforeach ($categories AS $cat) {%0a	$c_cat_name = htmlspecialchars($cat['name']);%0a	echo "\t%3coptgroup label=\"{$c_cat_name}\">\n";%0a%0a	foreach ($pages AS $page) {%0a		if ( $page['cat_id'] == $cat['id'] ) {%0a			$c_page_id = htmlspecialchars((int)$page['id']);%0a			$c_page_name = htmlspecialchars($page['name']);%0a			echo "\t\t%3coption value=\"{$c_page_id}\">{$c_page_name}%3c/option>\n";%0a		}%0a	}%0a	# Reset pages so you can loop through it again%0a	reset($pages);%0a	echo "\t%3c/optgroup>\n";%0a}%0a%0aecho "%3c/select>\n";%0a?>%0a(:sourceend:)%0a%0aWhich returns the following HTML:%0a%0a(:source lang=html4strict linenum tabwidth=4:)%0a%3cselect id="page_id">%0a	%3coptgroup label="cars">%0a		%3coption value="1">Neon%3c/option>%0a		%3coption value="2">Saturn%3c/option>%0a	%3c/optgroup>%0a	%3coptgroup label="trucks">%0a		%3coption value="3">F150%3c/option>%0a		%3coption value="4">Ram 2500%3c/option>%0a		%3coption value="5">Suzuki%3c/option>%0a	%3c/optgroup>%0a	%3coptgroup label="motorcycles">%0a		%3coption value="6">Honda%3c/option>%0a	%3c/optgroup>%0a%3c/select>%0a(:sourceend:)%0a%0a* [[http://portfolio.tamaratemple.com/phpexamples/optiongroup.php|Demo]]%0a%0a(:Summary:How to handle options if you've got a nested set of them: optgroup tag:)%0a(:Parent:(Technology.)HTML:)%0a(:IncludeMe:[[(Technology.)HTML]]:)%0a(:Categories:[[!Articles]]:)%0a(:Tags: html:)%0a(:tags-hide html :)%0a
